page.title: 10Tilshead Traffic Survey
page.content: Today we watched the traffic on the main road at the bottem of School Lane for 15 minutes. We started at 1.45pm. I was watching going east and west. We were pleased to see a{convoy of army {vehicles.}There were 14 cars going west. There were no motor cyclists or cyclists and no buses or coaches either. There were no buses or coaches because we came to late in the day. There were 7 lorries and 2 vans. There was a tractor and a tractor going east. The total number of vehicles which passed us was 43.
